<item>
            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-208] Zookeeper C client uses API that are not thread safe, causing crashes when multiple instances are active</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-208</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Zookeeper C client library uses gethostbyname and strtok, both of which are not safe to use from multiple threads.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is resolved by using getaddrinfo and strtok_r in place of the older API.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Linux&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
